remarks: Proof of a theorem that can act as a sole axiom for pure predicate calculus with ~ ax-gen as the inference rule.  This proof extends the idea of ~ axc5c711 and related theorems.  (Contributed by Andrew Salmon, 14-Jul-2011.)
statement: axc5c4c711 $p |- ( ( A. x A. y -. A. x A. y ( A. y ph -> ps ) -> ( ph -> A. y ( A. y ph -> ps ) ) ) -> ( A. y ph -> A. y ps ) ) $.
